The Balanced Scorecard Institute of South Africa (BSCISA) will present their 2021 Executive Programme (EP) on 16 July and 30 July at Technopark – Stellenbosch sponsored by Toyota Stellenbosch, Highberry Winery and SASFIN Bank. This Executive Programme (5 modules) is meant for corporate and public companies and institutions who need to dramatically increase their business performance by facilitating practical performance targets, delivering results by streamlining operations and building capacity through excellence services. Goals of this programme: Introducing the basics of Strategy; Build, Implement and manage with a Balanced Scorecard (BSC) System and Strategy Map. This will enable participants to develop the necessary skills and knowledge to implement a BSC. Programme: 16 July 08h00      Registration 08h30      Setting the scene 09h00      Introduction 09h15      Module 1: Business strategy based on five strategic  business questions/issues 10h30      Tea and refreshments 11h00      Module 2:  Introducing the BSC methodology 12h00     Module 3: Building the strategy map 13h00      Lunch 14h00     Module 4: Cascading the BSC 15h00     Module 5: Executing and aligning the BSC 16h30     Using the performance tracker tool (PTT) Draw of mystery prize and wine tasting. Programme: 30 July 8h00      Registration 9h00      Introduction Johan Hough and Rob Payne 9h15      Five important business questions 10h00    Strategy 10h30    Tea and refreshments 11h00     Strategy assessment as planning tool 2021 – 2025 12h00     Performance Tracker Tool (PTT) and strategy mapping tool (SMT) 13h00      Lunch (Sponsored by Toyota Stellenbosch) 14h00     High Performance Assessment Tool (HPAT) 15h00     Value curve tool (VCT) 16h00     Performance Matrix Tool Draw of mystery prize and wine tasting. The Balanced Scorecard Institute of South Africa (BSCISA) was formed in 1999 after discussions with Proff Kaplan and Norton from the Business School in Boston, Massachusetts, USA. The BSCISA owns four trademarks, BSC SA, BSCI AFRICA, BSC UK and BSC EUROPE. The new trademark will expire in November 2031. The BSCI trained 12 000 people and supported 130 organisations on 3 continents. Major consulting, training and research engagements include De Beers (Botswana), Anglo American (UK), World Economiuc Forum (Switzerland), MTN (Nigeria), Ecobank (Malawi), Swaziland Electricity Company, Zimbabwe Maixe Bag, PetroSA, Deloitte, Mango Airlines, Standard Bank, Capitec Bank, Stefanutti Stocks, V&A Waterfront, Vodacom and Key Mate. The value proposition of the BSCISA is to:  Align processes and actions with mission and vision, Create line-of-sight from KPA’s and KPI’s bases on mandates of boards, excos and senior management, Ensure that the right people are in the right place, and Create your future by applying the BSCISA strategy assessment and strategy mapping tools, performance assessment and tracker tools, and value curve tool. The BSCISA is the main sponsor for years of the international conference on information communication technologies in education. The BSCISA is your sustainable performance partner who will add value to your future (local and global) operations! Prof Johan Hough is the founding and managing partner since 1991 and the co-author of six books on strategy, global business and entrepreneurship. He is the strategy business developer for Ishango. College and MyElearning.Education and also involved with the Milpard Business School and False Bay College. For more information contact 082 452 4393 or visit www.balancedscorecardsa.co.za